post_text:
This is Anna from MVHS Music! Sharing a special message to our Spartans! Can you believe we’re only two weeks away?! Get ready for another wonderful school year. The halls and classrooms might be empty, but our hearts will be full as we resume remote instruction and once again make music together. So roll up your sleeves, take some deep breaths, start your long tones, and don’t forget your Spartan gear!
It’s going to be a great Fall, and I’m honored to share it with you.
See you soon ❤️

Stay tuned for some more good news!
#SmileWithYourEyes
#StrongerTogether💪

post_text:
Good morning MVLA families,

While we have no confirmed cases of the virus among students and staff, and the closure of our schools is an unprecedented action, it is going to be an important one in mitigating the spread of the virus in our community.

We will close schools effective Tuesday, March 17, for two weeks. We will evaluate the re-opening target of March 27, based on the status of the coronavirus situation. Our district is closed on Monday 3/16, and Tuesday 3/17 is a professional development day for staff, with no students in attendance.

Tuesday will be an important day for us as we work to complete the plans for flexible learning for our students. This is, as you know, uncharted territory for all of us, and we appreciate your support, patience, and flexibility.

For up to the minute information, please visit www.mvla.net

Thank you
Superintendent Dr. Nellie Meyer

post_text: Mountain View Athletics is proud to announce the 15 MVHS seniors who committed to play College Athletics next year. The list is deep and wide with commits in girls water polo, volleyball, soccer, softball, golf, diving, fencing, swimming, gymnastics as well as boys water polo and soccer. We would like to recognize the tireless effort of the MV coaches and Athletic Department that helped make it possible for our MV Student Athletes to compete and achieve at such a high level. Congratulations to the MV Class of 2020 for setting a new single year record with 15 college commits. #SpartyUpMVAthletics #SPARTANPRIDE

post_text: MVLA has learned of a cyber security breach on our systems – the latest in what has been a series of such attacks on school districts nationwide. We have taken immediate actions to protect our data and enhance security and have brought in forensic technology experts to help investigate. The attack has affected the ability of our schools to make and receive phone calls. Please visit MVLA.net for more detailed updates.

post_text: Amazing! What a wonderful way to spend an afternoon
shared_text:
MVHS Oracle is with Angela Mucha Tamada and 2 others.
January 28 at 9:48 AM ·

The whole school gathered in the gym this Monday, Jan. 28, to hold the annual cultural assembly. Students and teachers enjoyed performances that celebrated Nigerian culture, K-Pop, Mexican Folk-dancing, Japanese culture, Maori inspired singing and dancing, and Bollywood culture. We also saw a robotics club robot throw an oversized ball around and a duet of Lady Gaga’s “Shallow.”
